 883:Core/Src/port.c ****         /* Priority grouping:  The interrupt controller (NVIC) allows the bits
 884:Core/Src/port.c ****          * that define each interrupt's priority to be split between bits that
 885:Core/Src/port.c ****          * define the interrupt's pre-emption priority bits and bits that define
 886:Core/Src/port.c ****          * the interrupt's sub-priority.  For simplicity all bits must be defined
 887:Core/Src/port.c ****          * to be pre-emption priority bits.  The following assertion will fail if
 888:Core/Src/port.c ****          * this is not the case (if some bits represent a sub-priority).
 889:Core/Src/port.c ****          *
 890:Core/Src/port.c ****          * If the application only uses CMSIS libraries for interrupt
 891:Core/Src/port.c ****          * configuration then the correct setting can be achieved on all Cortex-M
 892:Core/Src/port.c ****          * devices by calling NVIC_SetPriorityGrouping( 0 ); before starting the
 893:Core/Src/port.c ****          * scheduler.  Note however that some vendor specific peripheral libraries
 894:Core/Src/port.c ****          * assume a non-zero priority group setting, in which cases using a value
 895:Core/Src/port.c ****          * of zero will result in unpredictable behaviour. */
 896:Core/Src/port.c ****         configASSERT( ( portAIRCR_REG & portPRIORITY_GROUP_MASK ) <= ulMaxPRIGROUPValue );
